This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as speech recognition and language translation. It may also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with audio data. Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques such as data augmentation and pre-trained weights, which are commonly used in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper may also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as speech recognition is a key component of many social and information network applications.
